The course deals with principles of economics and also explains the processes in the real economy both at micro-level (household and firm behavior) and macro-level (GDP and economic growth).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to present basic concepts of micro- and macroeconomics, and to introduce the fundamentals of economic processes at individual as well as aggregate levels.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the subject: * knows the logic of the structure of the micro- and macroeconomic models, the premises and the possible conclusions; * is able to explain optimal behavior of consumers and producers * is able to  explain functioning of firm in the market competition (cost, production quantity, pricing, other) * understands functioning of markets,  knows market theory, different market structures and externalities; * knows how to measure economic welfare and development (GDP and components) * is able to explain role of government in economy  * is familiar with developments in Estonian economy in the above-mentioned fields.
